  "text": "Butyrate was measured in the serum using a Varian Saturn 2000 GC-MS-MS using a published protocol [CITATION_1] ) with slight modifications. In brief, to 250 lL of serum, an equal volume of nuclease free water was added and acidified with 100 lL of 50% H 2 SO 4 . To the acidified samples, 5 lL of 3 mmol/L isobutyric acid was added as an internal standard. Butyrate was extracted by adding 500 lL of diethyl ether, vortexing for 30 sec, and quickly centrifuging at 5000 g. Five hundred lL of the upper ether layer was transferred to a fresh eppendorf tube and the extraction repeated two more times. One milliliter of the extract was transferred to a glass vial and derivatized with 250 lL of N-tert-Butyldimethylsilyl-Nmethyltrifluoroacetamide (MTBS-TFA). Samples were run on GC-MS-MS within 24 h.",
